Lacey Chabert is the latest "Mean Girls" star to strip down, posing for the November cover of Maxim in little more than a white bra and matching cover-up. The 31-year-old actress, who first hit the spotlight in "Party of Five" when she was 12, opens up to the magazine about life as a child star. "Look, life is tough, and growing up in this business is especially tough," she told Maxim.
